.Dd June 16, 2026
.Dt LIBTG 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm tg_tagset_init ,
.Nm tg_tagset_free ,
.Nm tg_tagset_parse ,
.Nm tg_tagset_add ,
.Nm tg_tagset_remove ,
.Nm tg_tagset_has ,
.Nm tg_tagset_render ,
.Nm tg_xattr_get ,
.Nm tg_xattr_set ,
.Nm tg_xattr_remove
.Nd tag-set and extended-attribute library
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libtg
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In tg/tagset.h
.Ft void
.Fn tg_tagset_init "TgTagSet *ts"
.Ft void
.Fn tg_tagset_free "TgTagSet *ts"
.Ft bool
.Fn tg_tagset_parse "TgTagSet *ts" "const char *value" "size_t len"
.Ft bool
.Fn tg_tagset_add "TgTagSet *ts" "const char *tag"
.Ft bool
.Fn tg_tagset_remove "TgTagSet *ts" "const char *tag"
.Ft bool
.Fn tg_tagset_has "const TgTagSet *ts" "const char *tag"
.Ft char *
.Fn tg_tagset_render "const TgTagSet *ts" "size_t *out_len"
.In tg/xattr.h
.Ft TgXattrResult
.Fn tg_xattr_get "const char *path" "char *buf" "size_t cap" "size_t *out_len"
.Ft TgXattrResult
.Fn tg_xattr_set "const char *path" "const char *value" "size_t len"
.Ft TgXattrResult
.Fn tg_xattr_remove "const char *path"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm libtg
is the engine behind
.Xr tg 1 ,
split into two independent layers.
.Pp
.Sy tagset
manages an in-memory set of tags and converts to and from the serialized,
comma-separated form described in
.Xr tg 5 .
A
.Vt TgTagSet
must be initialized with
.Fn tg_tagset_init
and released with
.Fn tg_tagset_free .
.Fn tg_tagset_parse
splits a stored
.Fa value
of
.Fa len
bytes (which need not be NUL-terminated) and merges the tags into
.Fa ts .
.Fn tg_tagset_add
and
.Fn tg_tagset_remove
return
.Dv true
when the set changed.
.Fn tg_tagset_render
returns a freshly
.Xr malloc 3 Ns -ed ,
NUL-terminated string such as
.Ql a,b,c ,
sorted and de-duplicated, and stores its length (excluding the NUL) in
.Fa *out_len ;
the caller frees it.
.Pp
.Sy xattr
reads and writes the
.Va user.tags
attribute, operating on the symbolic link itself rather than its target.
Values are byte buffers, not strings.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
The
.Fn tg_xattr_ *
functions return a
.Vt TgXattrResult :
.Dv TG_XATTR_OK
on success,
.Dv TG_XATTR_ABSENT
when the attribute is unset,
.Dv TG_XATTR_UNSUPPORTED ,
.Dv TG_XATTR_NOFILE ,
.Dv TG_XATTR_ACCESS ,
.Dv TG_XATTR_NOSPACE ,
.Dv TG_XATTR_TOOBIG ,
or
.Dv TG_XATTR_ERROR .
.Fn tg_tagset_render
returns
.Dv NULL
on allocation failure.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Link against the library with
.Xr pkg-config 1 :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
cc example.c $(pkg-config --cflags --libs tg)
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr tg 1 ,
.Xr tg 5
